            A fading pale sky just filled everything above, <br />
            no memory of what color it once was.<br>
            Too caught up in everything, with almost no room <br />
            left to notice anything at all.<br><br>
            
            Still reaching for something just beyond my sight.<br>
            I can't recall what I wanted before.<br>
            How do we live well when we don't even see inside?<br>
            Where do we go now? Do we even know?<br><br>
            
            If chasing ideals makes us fall apart,<br>
            maybe staying as we are is enough, just as we are right now.<br>
            We don’t always have to face ahead.<br>
            Just don't start to look down.<br><br>
            
            We all get lost. We all look back again.<br>
            Do we follow, or lose the track then?<br>
            Leave it undefined. Leave it out of sight.<br>
            No need to decide just yet.<br><br>
            
            A fading pale sky just filled everything above,<br />
            yet somehow it doesn't seem to stand still.<br>
            Just slowly letting go of trying to hold it all,<br>
            Finally, I find room to breathe.<br><br>
            
            Still wondering now a bit where we're meant to go,<br>
            but maybe it was never truly certain.<br>
            If I stop reaching for something better, maybe<br>
            I can stay right here.<br>
            Let it all be right here.<br><br>
            
            If chasing ideals makes us fall apart,<br>
            maybe we were whole all along,<br>
            just as we’ve always been.<br>
            We don’t always have to find a way.<br>
            Just don’t drift far away.<br><br>
            
            We all wander off. We all turn around again.<br>
            Do we lean in, or step aside then?<br>
            Leave it unsaid. Leave it as is.<br>
            No need to resolve just yet.
